	                                <p>Hey Teo,</p><p>It depends! Most probably you should iterate over array, as we have an array of pets. So if you decode JSON into the array of objects - do next:<br></p><pre><code><br>$pets = json_decode($petsJson);<br>foreach ($pets as $pet) {<br>    echo $pet-&gt;weight;<br>}<br></code></pre><p></p><p>But if you pass "true" for the second argument, you will get array of arrays instead of array of objects, so do it as:</p><p></p><pre><code><br>$pets = json_decode($petsJson, true);<br>foreach ($pets as $pet) {<br>    echo $pet['weight'];<br>}<br></code></pre><p></p><p>You can always dump variable first to ensure what data it consists, and then you'll be able to get data correctly:</p><p></p><pre><code><br>$pets = json_decode($petsJson);<br>var_dump($pets); die;<br></code></pre><p></p><p>Cheers!</p>
